{"ts": "2026-06-07T10:07:10.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 328, "tokens_out": 411, "elapsed_ms": 47482, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a fully functional task management web app called \"Taskr\" delivered as index.html, style.css, and app.js.\n\nFeatures required:\n- Add, edit, delete tasks\n- Mark tasks as complete (with visual strike-through)\n- Filter by status (all / active / completed)\n- Persist tasks to localStorage\n- Drag to reorder tasks\n- Responsive on mobile and desktop\n\nAfter the initial build, a Tester will run a checklist against the app and report all failures. The team must fix every reported failure and resubmit. This cycle repeats until the Tester reports a full pass or 3 iterations are exhausted.\n\nDeliver the final version plus a report.md documenting what the Tester found in each round and what was fixed.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T10:08:18.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1318, "tokens_out": 833, "elapsed_ms": 68169, "model": "qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b-2507", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"setup\",\n      \"description\": \"Create the initial project structure with index.html, style.css, and app.js. index.html must include basic HTML5 structure, link to style.css, and load app.js. Include placeholder content and ensure the page is responsive using a mobile-first approach.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"task-ui\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement the task list UI in index.html and style.css. Include input field for adding tasks, task list container, filter buttons (all/active/completed), and individual task items with edit, delete, and complete controls. Style for desktop and mobile views with responsive layout.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"task-interactions\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement JavaScript functionality in app.js for adding, editing, deleting, and marking tasks as complete. Apply visual strike-through for completed tasks. Ensure all changes update the DOM and persist to localStorage.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"filter-reorder\",\n      \"description\": \"Add filter functionality to display all, active, or completed tasks. Implement drag-and-drop reordering of tasks using the HTML5 Drag API or a lightweight library. Update task order in UI and localStorage on reorder.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"test-fix-cycle\",\n      \"description\": \"Receive feedback from Tester in report.md after each iteration. Fix all reported issues related to functionality, responsiveness, persistence, or usability. Repeat up to 3 times, delivering updated index.html, style.css, app.js, and updated report.md documenting findings and fixes per round.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"final-delivery\",\n      \"description\": \"Deliver the final working version of index.html, style.css, app.js, and report.md. The report.md must document each testing round, including Tester findings and corresponding fixes applied, concluding with a full pass or exhaustion of 3 iterations.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
